  "content": {
    "problemStatement": "### **Aptitude Practice Question**\n\nAn 80 m long ladder is leaning on a wall. If the ladder makes an angle of 45 degrees with the ground, find the distance of the ladder from the wall.<img alt=\"1\" height=\"265\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20260618114432714093/1.webp\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20260618114432714093/1.webp 279w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-conte\n\n---\n\n### **Answer & Explanation**\n\nnt/uploads/20260618114432714093/1-100.webp 100w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20260618114432714093/1-200.webp 200w\" width=\"279\"/> Here, cos \u03b8 = Base / Hypotenuse\n\u21d2 cos 45 = Base / 80\n\u21d2 Base = 80 cos 45 = 80 / \u221a2= 40 \u221a2\n\nThus, Distance of the ladder from the wall = 40 \u221a2 m",
    "sampleTestCases": []
  }
